Defendant Hayley M Burris in court, in custody, with attorney Jonathan A. Lavoy.   Pablo Galaviz appeared for the State of Wisconsin.

Sentencing argument by the State.  Sentencing argument by Atty. Lavoy.  Statement by mother.  Statement by father.  Statement by the defendant.  

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed  Sentence of:

60 months  Imprisonment (Credit - 32 days )  CONCURRENT TO MILWAUKEE COUNTY SENTENCE
- 24 months of Initial Confinement
- 36 months of Extended Supervision

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
- AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Mental Health Evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- Be involved in a 12 step program 2 times a week.  Obtain a sponsor/mentor within 30 days.  Start attended within 1 week of release.
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Perform  20 hours of community service each year of extended supervision;
- Maintain a valid driver's license;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment;
- No contact with co-defendant;
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge.

